{
  "stem": "14724.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 24.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were tables set out with different names of different towns in Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at Kassel's table there were only three of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One lady who was five years older than me, and one who was four years younger than me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we started to chat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course, I'd never been back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the one younger than I had come to non-Jewish people in Scotland, and had never been back to Kassel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But she said she would go back for me, because I couldn't go back, to see what she could find out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She brought me back to book, a commemorative book which Kassel had printed, which gave the names of all my family that died, [? and ?] [? even ?] photographs of two of my brothers.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --I decided, eventually, that I must go back and find out exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And a friend who lives in Australia came with me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name is [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ed. ?] Because the two friends from Kassel, one couldn't speak German any more than I could.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other one still had friends in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I needed different company.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, we went to Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we ended up in-- in-- in Kassel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, through this Scottish friend-- I'm sorry, it gets complicated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Through this Scottish friend, I had come to know a lady in Kassel who was part of the university.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And when I got to Kassel, I had to phone her.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we took her out for a meal, and then tried to work out a way to get to Hof.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Which was very difficult, because there was only one bus a day to Hof from Kassel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she had no idea if there were any coming back.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
